Species not very variable (see 
Table 1
and 
Appendix 3
). Minimum height 1.27 (from North coast of Rurutu, 
250- 302 m
); maximum height 2.40 (from Mont Ari’i Moana, 
614-664 m
). Variable number of axial ribs: 16-27. In about 10% of specimens examined, the external lip presents a more or less conspicuous angulation (
Fig. 4G
). The axial ribs are thinner when they are more numerous.
